      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's natural to feel overwhelmed by the vastness of entropy and the ultimate end of things. In the face of such vastness, finding meaning often comes from the small, immediate moments of connection and experience. Perhaps finding purpose in the effort itself—the act of living and creating—can offer a gentle antidote to that feeling of futility. Don't feel pressured to find one giant, cosmic reason; sometimes the value is in the present moment.",
