    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but \"vibrancy\" is just another way of describing the friction before the inevitable. it's exhausting. it feels more like a burden to keep pushing through the dark for the sake of a \"fleeting moment\" that doesn't even matter in the long run. why is it so important to keep struggling against something that's already decided?",
